having a life crisis|raw|<div class="infobox"> You joined Board Games</div>|raw|<div class="infobox infobox-roomintro"><div class="infobox-limited"><div style="height: 200px; background: url('https://i.postimg.cc/g0ZWJw6w/image.png');"><center style="padding-top: 1%;"><strong style="font-size: 2em; color: #ccc;"><em>Welcome to Board Games!</em></strong></center><details style="color: #ccc; margin-left: 2.3%; padding: 8px 0.7%; text-align: left; height: 79px;" open=""> <summary style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 2px; color: #ccc;">Game of a lifetime: Catan: Seafarers (click to expand)</summary><div style="height: 60px; overflow: auto;">Catan: Seafarers, is an expansion of the board game Catan. The main feature of this expansion is the addition of ships, gold rivers, and the pirate to the game, allowing play between multiple islands. The expansion also provides numerous scenarios, some of which have custom rules. The Seafarers rules and scenarios are also, for the most part, compatible with Catan: Cities &amp; Knights and Catan: Traders &amp; Barbarians.</div></details><center style="padding-top: 7px;"><a href="https://discord.gg/XzyMJJc"><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578722849431486483/unknown.png') no-repeat; height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px;"></button></a><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578722951730298891/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;" name="send" value="/rules"></button><a href="https://www.smogon.com/forums/threads/board-game-based-meta-games.3580005/"><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578723013399412737/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;"></button></a><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578728643841490955/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;" name="send" value="/roomfaq games"></button></center></div></div></div>|raw||raw|<div class="infobox">(Staff intro:)<br /><div><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">Staff Stuff</b></summary><br /><h3>To-Do:</h3>a) Update roomintro (new intro MUST contain Catan: Seafarers).<br />b) Start work on guides and quickstarts for the games we play.<br /><br /><h3>Games to be added:</h3>Battleship, Lines of Action<br /><br /><h3>Moderation:</h3>As of yet, we haven't faced too many issues with moderation. Obvious trolls can be punished depending on severity at your discretion. For suspected engine usage, regular misconduct, and ragequitting, please bring up the issue in the staff channels on Discord. </details><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">PartBot</b></summary><hr /><details><summary>Chess</summary><b>,chess new</b> to make one, <b>,chess sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute (any order works), and <b>,chess menu</b> to open the menu. The <b>End</b> and <b>Stash</b> options allow you to end games, or store them for later. To restore a game from a backup/stash, use <b>,chess backups</b>.<br />When to make one: Always</details><hr /><details><summary>Othello</summary><b>,othello new</b> to make one, <b>,othello sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute (any order works), and <b>,othello menu</b> to open the menu. The <b>End</b> and <b>Stash</b> options allow you to end games, or store them for later. To restore a game from a backup/stash, use <b>,othello backups</b>.<br />When to make one: Always</details><hr /><details><summary>Scrabble</summary><b>Broken</b>, will be repaired soon.</details><hr /><details><summary>Chain Reaction</summary><b>,chainreaction new (height)x(length)</b> to make one (dimensions are optional), <b>,chainreaction start</b> to start it (once enough players have joined), <b>,chainreaction sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute people, <b>,chainreaction dq (user)</b> to disqualify a user, and <b>,chainreaction end</b> to end a game early. Supports 2-8 players.<br />When to make one: When 3-4 users seem interested.</details><hr /><details><summary>Exploding Voltorb</summary><b>,explodingvoltorb new</b> to make one, <b>,explodingvoltorb start</b> to start it (once enough players have joined), <b>,explodingvoltorb sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute people, and <b>,explodingvoltorb end</b> to end a game early. Supports 2-5 players. Note: Remember to pull up <b>,explodingvoltorb help</b> and make sure the users know how to play; this is a bit command-reliant.<br />When to make one: When 3-4 users seem interested.</details><hr /><details><summary>Blackjack</summary>Probably won't need to, but it's <b>,blackjack new (optional autostart in seconds)</b>, <b>,blackjack start</b>, <b>,hit</b>, <b>,stay</b>, and <b>,blackjack end</b>.</details><hr /><br />Doing <b>,help (game)</b> or <b>,(game) help</b> displays the help for the corresponding, too.</details><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">Global Staff</b></summary>First up, welcome to Board Games! :3<br/>As global staff, you might be pinged every now and then by users who want to start games while there's no roomstaff online (or by users who don't yet know the difference between them). If you're free, starting a game is as simple as doing <code>,game new</code> (single-player games can be created without staff, two-player games automatically start when both players join, and multiplayer ones are started via <code>,game start</code>). If you feel someone is breaking room/global rules, feel free to act at your own discretion.<br/>For a more helpful guide for the various commands used for games, there's a couple entries in the <b>Staff Stuff</b> section above, and in the #bot-commands channel on Discord (to be added).</details></div>>boardgames|uhtml|poll79|<div class="infobox"><p style="margin: 2px 0 5px 0"><span The main feature of this expansion is the addition of ships, gold rivers, and the pirate to the game, allowing play between multiple islands. The expansion also provides numerous scenarios, some of which have custom rules. The Seafarers rules and scenarios are also, for the most part, compatible with Catan: Cities &amp; Knights and Catan: Traders &amp; Barbarians.</div></details><center style="padding-top: 7px;"><a href="https://discord.gg/XzyMJJc"><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578722849431486483/unknown.png') no-repeat; height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px;"></button></a><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578722951730298891/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;" name="send" value="/rules"></button><a href="https://www.smogon.com/forums/threads/board-game-based-meta-games.3580005/"><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578723013399412737/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;"></button></a><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578728643841490955/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;" name="send" value="/roomfaq games"></button></center></div></div></div>|raw||raw|<div class="infobox">(Staff intro:)<br /><div><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">Staff Stuff</b></summary><br /><h3>To-Do:</h3>a) Update roomintro (new intro MUST contain Catan: Seafarers).<br />b) Start work on guides and quickstarts for the games we play.<br /><br /><h3>Games to be added:</h3>Battleship, Lines of Action<br /><br /><h3>Moderation:</h3>As of yet, we haven't faced too many issues with moderation. Obvious trolls can be punished depending on severity at your discretion. For suspected engine usage, regular misconduct, and ragequitting, please bring up the issue in the staff channels on Discord. </details><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">PartBot</b></summary><hr /><details><summary>Chess</summary><b>,chess new</b> to make one, <b>,chess sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute (any order works), and <b>,chess menu</b> to open the menu. The <b>End</b> and <b>Stash</b> options allow you to end games, or store them for later. To restore a game from a backup/stash, use <b>,chess backups</b>.<br />When to make one: Always</details><hr /><details><summary>Othello</summary><b>,othello new</b> to make one, <b>,othello sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute (any order works), and <b>,othello menu</b> to open the menu. The <b>End</b> and <b>Stash</b> options allow you to end games, or store them for later. To restore a game from a backup/stash, use <b>,othello backups</b>.<br />When to make one: Always</details><hr /><details><summary>Scrabble</summary><b>Broken</b>, will be repaired soon.</details><hr /><details><summary>Chain Reaction</summary><b>,chainreaction new (height)x(length)</b> to make one (dimensions are optional), <b>,chainreaction start</b> to start it (once enough players have joined), <b>,chainreaction sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute people, <b>,chainreaction dq (user)</b> to disqualify a user, and <b>,chainreaction end</b> to end a game early. Supports 2-8 players.<br />When to make one: When 3-4 users seem interested.</details><hr /><details><summary>Exploding Voltorb</summary><b>,explodingvoltorb new</b> to make one, <b>,explodingvoltorb start</b> to start it (once enough players have joined), <b>,explodingvoltorb sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute people, and <b>,explodingvoltorb end</b> to end a game early. Supports 2-5 players. Note: Remember to pull up <b>,explodingvoltorb help</b> and make sure the users know how to play; this is a bit command-reliant.<br />When to make one: When 3-4 users seem interested.</details><hr /><details><summary>Blackjack</summary>Probably won't need to, but it's <b>,blackjack new (optional autostart in seconds)</b>, <b>,blackjack start</b>, <b>,hit</b>, <b>,stay</b>, and <b>,blackjack end</b>.</details><hr /><br />Doing <b>,help (game)</b> or <b>,(game) help</b> displays the help for the corresponding, too.</details><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">Global Staff</b></summary>First up, welcome to Board Games! :3<br/>As global staff, you might be pinged every now and then by users who want to start games while there's no roomstaff online (or by users who don't yet know the difference between them). If you're free, starting a game is as simple as doing <code>,game new</code> (single-player games can be created without staff, two-player games automatically start when both players join, and multiplayer ones are started via <code>,game start</code>). If you feel someone is breaking room/global rules, feel free to act at your own discretion.<br/>For a more helpful guide for the various commands used for games, there's a couple entries in the <b>Staff Stuff</b> section above, and in the #bot-commands channel on Discord (to be added).</details></div>>boardgames|uhtml|poll79|<div class="infobox"><p style="margin: 2px 0 5px 0"><span The main feature of this expansion is the addition of ships, gold rivers, and the pirate to the game, allowing play between multiple islands. The expansion also provides numerous scenarios, some of which have custom rules. The Seafarers rules and scenarios are also, for the most part, compatible with Catan: Cities &amp; Knights and Catan: Traders &amp; Barbarians.</div></details><center style="padding-top: 7px;"><a href="https://discord.gg/XzyMJJc"><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578722849431486483/unknown.png') no-repeat; height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px;"></button></a><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578722951730298891/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;" name="send" value="/rules"></button><a href="https://www.smogon.com/forums/threads/board-game-based-meta-games.3580005/"><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578723013399412737/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;"></button></a><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578728643841490955/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;" name="send" value="/roomfaq games"></button></center></div></div></div>|raw||raw|<div class="infobox">(Staff intro:)<br /><div><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">Staff Stuff</b></summary><br /><h3>To-Do:</h3>a) Update roomintro (new intro MUST contain Catan: Seafarers).<br />b) Start work on guides and quickstarts for the games we play.<br /><br /><h3>Games to be added:</h3>Battleship, Lines of Action<br /><br /><h3>Moderation:</h3>As of yet, we haven't faced too many issues with moderation. Obvious trolls can be punished depending on severity at your discretion. For suspected engine usage, regular misconduct, and ragequitting, please bring up the issue in the staff channels on Discord. </details><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">PartBot</b></summary><hr /><details><summary>Chess</summary><b>,chess new</b> to make one, <b>,chess sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute (any order works), and <b>,chess menu</b> to open the menu. The <b>End</b> and <b>Stash</b> options allow you to end games, or store them for later. To restore a game from a backup/stash, use <b>,chess backups</b>.<br />When to make one: Always</details><hr /><details><summary>Othello</summary><b>,othello new</b> to make one, <b>,othello sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute (any order works), and <b>,othello menu</b> to open the menu. The <b>End</b> and <b>Stash</b> options allow you to end games, or store them for later. To restore a game from a backup/stash, use <b>,othello backups</b>.<br />When to make one: Always</details><hr /><details><summary>Scrabble</summary><b>Broken</b>, will be repaired soon.</details><hr /><details><summary>Chain Reaction</summary><b>,chainreaction new (height)x(length)</b> to make one (dimensions are optional), <b>,chainreaction start</b> to start it (once enough players have joined), <b>,chainreaction sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute people, <b>,chainreaction dq (user)</b> to disqualify a user, and <b>,chainreaction end</b> to end a game early. Supports 2-8 players.<br />When to make one: When 3-4 users seem interested.</details><hr /><details><summary>Exploding Voltorb</summary><b>,explodingvoltorb new</b> to make one, <b>,explodingvoltorb start</b> to start it (once enough players have joined), <b>,explodingvoltorb sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute people, and <b>,explodingvoltorb end</b> to end a game early. Supports 2-5 players. Note: Remember to pull up <b>,explodingvoltorb help</b> and make sure the users know how to play; this is a bit command-reliant.<br />When to make one: When 3-4 users seem interested.</details><hr /><details><summary>Blackjack</summary>Probably won't need to, but it's <b>,blackjack new (optional autostart in seconds)</b>, <b>,blackjack start</b>, <b>,hit</b>, <b>,stay</b>, and <b>,blackjack end</b>.</details><hr /><br />Doing <b>,help (game)</b> or <b>,(game) help</b> displays the help for the corresponding, too.</details><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">Global Staff</b></summary>First up, welcome to Board Games! :3<br/>As global staff, you might be pinged every now and then by users who want to start games while there's no roomstaff online (or by users who don't yet know the difference between them). If you're free, starting a game is as simple as doing <code>,game new</code> (single-player games can be created without staff, two-player games automatically start when both players join, and multiplayer ones are started via <code>,game start</code>). If you feel someone is breaking room/global rules, feel free to act at your own discretion.<br/>For a more helpful guide for the various commands used for games, there's a couple entries in the <b>Staff Stuff</b> section above, and in the #bot-commands channel on Discord (to be added).</details></div>>boardgames|uhtml|poll79|<div class="infobox"><p style="margin: 2px 0 5px 0"><span The main feature of this expansion is the addition of ships, gold rivers, and the pirate to the game, allowing play between multiple islands. The expansion also provides numerous scenarios, some of which have custom rules. The Seafarers rules and scenarios are also, for the most part, compatible with Catan: Cities &amp; Knights and Catan: Traders &amp; Barbarians.</div></details><center style="padding-top: 7px;"><a href="https://discord.gg/XzyMJJc"><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578722849431486483/unknown.png') no-repeat; height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px;"></button></a><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578722951730298891/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;" name="send" value="/rules"></button><a href="https://www.smogon.com/forums/threads/board-game-based-meta-games.3580005/"><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578723013399412737/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;"></button></a><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578728643841490955/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;" name="send" value="/roomfaq games"></button></center></div></div></div>|raw||raw|<div class="infobox">(Staff intro:)<br /><div><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">Staff Stuff</b></summary><br /><h3>To-Do:</h3>a) Update roomintro (new intro MUST contain Catan: Seafarers).<br />b) Start work on guides and quickstarts for the games we play.<br /><br /><h3>Games to be added:</h3>Battleship, Lines of Action<br /><br /><h3>Moderation:</h3>As of yet, we haven't faced too many issues with moderation. Obvious trolls can be punished depending on severity at your discretion. For suspected engine usage, regular misconduct, and ragequitting, please bring up the issue in the staff channels on Discord. </details><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">PartBot</b></summary><hr /><details><summary>Chess</summary><b>,chess new</b> to make one, <b>,chess sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute (any order works), and <b>,chess menu</b> to open the menu. The <b>End</b> and <b>Stash</b> options allow you to end games, or store them for later. To restore a game from a backup/stash, use <b>,chess backups</b>.<br />When to make one: Always</details><hr /><details><summary>Othello</summary><b>,othello new</b> to make one, <b>,othello sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute (any order works), and <b>,othello menu</b> to open the menu. The <b>End</b> and <b>Stash</b> options allow you to end games, or store them for later. To restore a game from a backup/stash, use <b>,othello backups</b>.<br />When to make one: Always</details><hr /><details><summary>Scrabble</summary><b>Broken</b>, will be repaired soon.</details><hr /><details><summary>Chain Reaction</summary><b>,chainreaction new (height)x(length)</b> to make one (dimensions are optional), <b>,chainreaction start</b> to start it (once enough players have joined), <b>,chainreaction sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute people, <b>,chainreaction dq (user)</b> to disqualify a user, and <b>,chainreaction end</b> to end a game early. Supports 2-8 players.<br />When to make one: When 3-4 users seem interested.</details><hr /><details><summary>Exploding Voltorb</summary><b>,explodingvoltorb new</b> to make one, <b>,explodingvoltorb start</b> to start it (once enough players have joined), <b>,explodingvoltorb sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute people, and <b>,explodingvoltorb end</b> to end a game early. Supports 2-5 players. Note: Remember to pull up <b>,explodingvoltorb help</b> and make sure the users know how to play; this is a bit command-reliant.<br />When to make one: When 3-4 users seem interested.</details><hr /><details><summary>Blackjack</summary>Probably won't need to, but it's <b>,blackjack new (optional autostart in seconds)</b>, <b>,blackjack start</b>, <b>,hit</b>, <b>,stay</b>, and <b>,blackjack end</b>.</details><hr /><br />Doing <b>,help (game)</b> or <b>,(game) help</b> displays the help for the corresponding, too.</details><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">Global Staff</b></summary>First up, welcome to Board Games! :3<br/>As global staff, you might be pinged every now and then by users who want to start games while there's no roomstaff online (or by users who don't yet know the difference between them). If you're free, starting a game is as simple as doing <code>,game new</code> (single-player games can be created without staff, two-player games automatically start when both players join, and multiplayer ones are started via <code>,game start</code>). If you feel someone is breaking room/global rules, feel free to act at your own discretion.<br/>For a more helpful guide for the various commands used for games, there's a couple entries in the <b>Staff Stuff</b> section above, and in the #bot-commands channel on Discord (to be added).</details></div>>boardgames|uhtml|poll79|<div class="infobox"><p style="margin: 2px 0 5px 0"><span The main feature of this expansion is the addition of ships, gold rivers, and the pirate to the game, allowing play between multiple islands. The expansion also provides numerous scenarios, some of which have custom rules. The Seafarers rules and scenarios are also, for the most part, compatible with Catan: Cities &amp; Knights and Catan: Traders &amp; Barbarians.</div></details><center style="padding-top: 7px;"><a href="https://discord.gg/XzyMJJc"><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578722849431486483/unknown.png') no-repeat; height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px;"></button></a><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578722951730298891/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;" name="send" value="/rules"></button><a href="https://www.smogon.com/forums/threads/board-game-based-meta-games.3580005/"><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578723013399412737/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;"></button></a><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578728643841490955/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;" name="send" value="/roomfaq games"></button></center></div></div></div>|raw||raw|<div class="infobox">(Staff intro:)<br /><div><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">Staff Stuff</b></summary><br /><h3>To-Do:</h3>a) Update roomintro (new intro MUST contain Catan: Seafarers).<br />b) Start work on guides and quickstarts for the games we play.<br /><br /><h3>Games to be added:</h3>Battleship, Lines of Action<br /><br /><h3>Moderation:</h3>As of yet, we haven't faced too many issues with moderation. Obvious trolls can be punished depending on severity at your discretion. For suspected engine usage, regular misconduct, and ragequitting, please bring up the issue in the staff channels on Discord. </details><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">PartBot</b></summary><hr /><details><summary>Chess</summary><b>,chess new</b> to make one, <b>,chess sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute (any order works), and <b>,chess menu</b> to open the menu. The <b>End</b> and <b>Stash</b> options allow you to end games, or store them for later. To restore a game from a backup/stash, use <b>,chess backups</b>.<br />When to make one: Always</details><hr /><details><summary>Othello</summary><b>,othello new</b> to make one, <b>,othello sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute (any order works), and <b>,othello menu</b> to open the menu. The <b>End</b> and <b>Stash</b> options allow you to end games, or store them for later. To restore a game from a backup/stash, use <b>,othello backups</b>.<br />When to make one: Always</details><hr /><details><summary>Scrabble</summary><b>Broken</b>, will be repaired soon.</details><hr /><details><summary>Chain Reaction</summary><b>,chainreaction new (height)x(length)</b> to make one (dimensions are optional), <b>,chainreaction start</b> to start it (once enough players have joined), <b>,chainreaction sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute people, <b>,chainreaction dq (user)</b> to disqualify a user, and <b>,chainreaction end</b> to end a game early. Supports 2-8 players.<br />When to make one: When 3-4 users seem interested.</details><hr /><details><summary>Exploding Voltorb</summary><b>,explodingvoltorb new</b> to make one, <b>,explodingvoltorb start</b> to start it (once enough players have joined), <b>,explodingvoltorb sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute people, and <b>,explodingvoltorb end</b> to end a game early. Supports 2-5 players. Note: Remember to pull up <b>,explodingvoltorb help</b> and make sure the users know how to play; this is a bit command-reliant.<br />When to make one: When 3-4 users seem interested.</details><hr /><details><summary>Blackjack</summary>Probably won't need to, but it's <b>,blackjack new (optional autostart in seconds)</b>, <b>,blackjack start</b>, <b>,hit</b>, <b>,stay</b>, and <b>,blackjack end</b>.</details><hr /><br />Doing <b>,help (game)</b> or <b>,(game) help</b> displays the help for the corresponding, too.</details><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">Global Staff</b></summary>First up, welcome to Board Games! :3<br/>As global staff, you might be pinged every now and then by users who want to start games while there's no roomstaff online (or by users who don't yet know the difference between them). If you're free, starting a game is as simple as doing <code>,game new</code> (single-player games can be created without staff, two-player games automatically start when both players join, and multiplayer ones are started via <code>,game start</code>). If you feel someone is breaking room/global rules, feel free to act at your own discretion.<br/>For a more helpful guide for the various commands used for games, there's a couple entries in the <b>Staff Stuff</b> section above, and in the #bot-commands channel on Discord (to be added).</details></div>>boardgames|uhtml|poll79|<div class="infobox"><p style="margin: 2px 0 5px 0"><span The expansion also provides numerous scenarios, some of which have custom rules. The Seafarers rules and scenarios are also, for the most part, compatible with Catan: Cities &amp; Knights and Catan: Traders &amp; Barbarians.</div></details><center style="padding-top: 7px;"><a href="https://discord.gg/XzyMJJc"><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578722849431486483/unknown.png') no-repeat; height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px;"></button></a><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578722951730298891/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;" name="send" value="/rules"></button><a href="https://www.smogon.com/forums/threads/board-game-based-meta-games.3580005/"><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578723013399412737/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;"></button></a><button style="background: url('https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/400040026659880961/578728643841490955/unknown.png'); height: 57px; width: 121px; border-radius: 7px; border: 0px; margin-left: 2%;" name="send" value="/roomfaq games"></button></center></div></div></div>

|raw|<div class="infobox">(Staff intro:)<br /><div><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">Staff Stuff</b></summary><br /><h3>To-Do:</h3>a) Update roomintro (new intro MUST contain Catan: Seafarers).<br />b) Start work on guides and quickstarts for the games we play.<br /><br /><h3>Games to be added:</h3>Battleship, Lines of Action<br /><br /><h3>Moderation:</h3>As of yet, we haven't faced too many issues with moderation. Obvious trolls can be punished depending on severity at your discretion. For suspected engine usage, regular misconduct, and ragequitting, please bring up the issue in the staff channels on Discord. </details><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">PartBot</b></summary><hr /><details><summary>Chess</summary><b>,chess new</b> to make one, <b>,chess sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute (any order works), and <b>,chess menu</b> to open the menu. The <b>End</b> and <b>Stash</b> options allow you to end games, or store them for later. To restore a game from a backup/stash, use <b>,chess backups</b>.<br />When to make one: Always</details><hr /><details><summary>Othello</summary><b>,othello new</b> to make one, <b>,othello sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute (any order works), and <b>,othello menu</b> to open the menu. The <b>End</b> and <b>Stash</b> options allow you to end games, or store them for later. To restore a game from a backup/stash, use <b>,othello backups</b>.<br />When to make one: Always</details><hr /><details><summary>Scrabble</summary><b>Broken</b>, will be repaired soon.</details><hr /><details><summary>Chain Reaction</summary><b>,chainreaction new (height)x(length)</b> to make one (dimensions are optional), <b>,chainreaction start</b> to start it (once enough players have joined), <b>,chainreaction sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute people, <b>,chainreaction dq (user)</b> to disqualify a user, and <b>,chainreaction end</b> to end a game early. Supports 2-8 players.<br />When to make one: When 3-4 users seem interested.</details><hr /><details><summary>Exploding Voltorb</summary><b>,explodingvoltorb new</b> to make one, <b>,explodingvoltorb start</b> to start it (once enough players have joined), <b>,explodingvoltorb sub (user), (other user)</b> to substitute people, and <b>,explodingvoltorb end</b> to end a game early. Supports 2-5 players. Note: Remember to pull up <b>,explodingvoltorb help</b> and make sure the users know how to play; this is a bit command-reliant.<br />When to make one: When 3-4 users seem interested.</details><hr /><details><summary>Blackjack</summary>Probably won't need to, but it's <b>,blackjack new (optional autostart in seconds)</b>, <b>,blackjack start</b>, <b>,hit</b>, <b>,stay</b>, and <b>,blackjack end</b>.</details><hr /><br />Doing <b>,help (game)</b> or <b>,(game) help</b> displays the help for the corresponding, too.</details><details style="border: 1px solid; padding: 10px;"><summary><b style="font-size: 1.3em;">Global Staff</b></summary>First up, welcome to Board Games! :3<br/>As global staff, you might be pinged every now and then by users who want to start games while there's no roomstaff online (or by users who don't yet know the difference between them). If you're free, starting a game is as simple as doing <code>,game new</code> (single-player games can be created without staff, two-player games automatically start when both players join, and multiplayer ones are started via <code>,game start</code>). If you feel someone is breaking room/global rules, feel free to act at your own discretion.<br/>For a more helpful guide for the various commands used for games, there's a couple entries in the <b>Staff Stuff</b> section above, and in the #bot-commands channel on Discord (to be added).</details></div>
>boardgames
